\title{Square root of a linear operator}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-10}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{[[axler-1996-linear]] Definition 7.34}
\meta{source}{[[lankham-2016-linear]] Section 11.5}

\p{Let #{V} be an [[vectsp-0020]]s over #{\FF}. Let #{L,R\in\mathcal{L}(V)} be a linear operator. We say #{R} is a \define{square root} of #{L} if #{L=R^{2}}.}